thread.title: U.S. Government Bonds Make Gains

author: Gunjan Banerji
title: U.S. Government Bonds Make Gains
text:
U.S. government bonds strengthened Friday, building on gains posted Thursday after investors began buying bonds with yields near their highest levels for the year.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note fell for the second consecutive day to 2.877%, according to Tradeweb, from 2.893% on Thursday. Yields fall as bond prices rise.
